This paper discusses the design and detection of Hardware Trojans, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of Electronic Design Automation (EDA) tools, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of IP cores in hardware design, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the use of hardware design principles, which falls under the category of embedded systems (cs.ET) and systems and control (cs.SY).
